					<iframe title="header-video-musk-oxen-hcn" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/906862091?app_id=122963&background=1&controls=0&autoplay=1&mute=1" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" frameborder="0"></iframe>				</div>

				
					<div class="post-thumbnail-caption hero-video-caption">Muskoxen were reintroduced to Alaska’s Seward Peninsula decades ago, and their human neighbors have conflicted feelings about the formidable animals, which are a source of both meat and safety concerns. Video by NorwayStock/Shutterstock</div>

					
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">In Nome, Where the Muskoxen Roam … Controversially</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">In Alaska, residents are negotiating a contentious relationship with muskoxen, which were introduced to the area decades ago without local consent.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by Megan Gannon/High Country News 								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						February 5, 2024 | 4,000 words, about 20 minutes					</aside>
				</header>

